  "response_text": "# Budget-Friendly Cholesterol-Lowering Foods\n\n**Cheapest staples to prioritize:**\n- **Oats** (bulk bin or store brand) - soluble fiber helps lower cholesterol\n- **Beans & lentils** (dried, bulk) - cheap protein, high fiber\n- **Canned fish** (sardines, mackerel) - omega-3s, often on sale\n- **Eggs** - affordable protein; newer research is less restrictive about them\n- **Frozen vegetables** - often cheaper than fresh, same nutrients\n- **Brown rice** (bulk) - whole grain fiber\n\n**Budget tips:**\n- Buy store brands and bulk items\n- Watch for sales on canned goods\n- Dried beans/lentils cost pennies per serving\n- Skip expensive \"heart healthy\" branded products\n- Use food banks or community programs if available\n\n**What to limit on any budget:**\n- Fried foods\n- Processed meats\n- Sugary items\n- Butter and full-fat dairy (though small amounts are okay)\n\n**Free/low-cost additions:**\n- Walking 20-30 minutes daily helps as much as diet alone\n- Check if your doctor/clinic offers nutrition counseling\n\nThe good news: cholesterol-lowering foods tend to be among the cheapest—beans, oats, and frozen vegetables are budget winners anyway.\n\nWould specific meal ideas or recipes help?",
